  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What percentage of commission do sellers need to pay e-commerce websites like Flipkart, eBay, Amazon, Shopclues, Shimply, Myntra etc., when selling clothing such as t-shirts?",
  "response": "The commission rates for selling clothing like t-shirts on e-commerce platforms can vary based on several factors including the platform itself, the category of the product, and sometimes the seller's agreement with the platform. Below are general commission rates for selling t-shirts on some popular e-commerce websites:\n\n1. **Amazon**:\n   - Amazon's commission rates can vary, but for clothing items like t-shirts, the typical rate is around 15% to 18% of the selling price.\n\n2. **Flipkart**:\n   - Flipkart charges a commission of around 15% to 20% on clothing items, including t-shirts.\n\n3. **eBay**:\n   - eBay's fee structure is slightly different. It includes a final value fee, which is typically around 10% of the total amount of the sale (including shipping), and a small insertion fee for listing items. For clothing like t-shirts, you can expect to pay around 10% to 12% in total fees.\n\n4. **Shopclues**:\n   - Shopclues typically charges a commission of around 10% to 15% on clothing items.\n\n5. **Myntra**:\n   - Myntra, which is owned by Flipkart, has a similar commission structure. You can expect to pay around 15% to 20% on clothing sales.\n\n6. **Shimply**:\n   - Shimply's commission rates can vary, but for clothing items, they typically charge around 10% to 15%.\n\nPlease note that these rates are approximate and can change. It's always a good idea to check the most current fee structures on the respective websites or contact their seller support for the latest information. Additionally, these commissions do not include other potential fees like payment gateway charges, shipping, or promotional costs.",
